---
title: Pearl Pasta e Fagioli Soup with Toasted Panko & Parmesan
description: This soul-warming vegetarian soup is the culinary equivalent of a cozy blanket. It’s chock full of goodness, with earthy cannellini beans (aka fagioli), springy couscous (aka pearl pasta), and tender carrot, celery, and scallions, in a savory tomato broth with a pinch of chili flakes. Top with a sprinkle of nutty Parmesan and crisp toasted breadcrumbs, and you’ve got an ideal dinner or lunch! Get ready to wrap yourself in this meal that’s as satisfying and comforting as it is delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/655b735ad1348f59373b1b52-9edfdd81.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/655b735ad1348f59373b1b52.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 11 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 97 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pearl-pasta-e-fagioli-soup-655b735ad1348f59373b1b52
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{3%cloves}. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, whites and greens separated). Peel and dice @carrots{6%ounce}(peeled and diced into ¼-inch pieces). Dice @celery{2.5%ounce}(diced into ¼-inch pieces).

In a #large pot{}, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add carrots and celery; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1%unit}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @cannellini beans{1% can} and their liquid, @veggie stock concentrate{2%unit}, 2 cups water (4 cups for 4 servings), @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Cook, scraping any browned bits from bottom of pot, until flavors meld, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} to soup; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until couscous is tender and soup has thickened slightly, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium pan{}, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} over medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and a pinch of salt and pepper; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, toasted panko, scallion greens, and a pinch of pepper to taste. Serve.